1
00:00:01,535 --> 00:00:03,723
When within the first few days of joining,

2
00:00:03,723 --> 00:00:06,831
when I joined in San Francisco in 1971,

3
00:00:06,831 --> 00:00:10,912
the devotees would tell, you know,
‘Prabhupād said …’ Prabhupād stories,

4
00:00:10,912 --> 00:00:13,205
[A Chance for Everyone]

5
00:00:13,580 --> 00:00:18,508
one of which was: Prabhupād said,
when someone newly joins and comes,

6
00:00:18,508 --> 00:00:20,905
that Rādhārāṇī goes to Kṛṣṇa and says,

7
00:00:20,905 --> 00:00:25,951
“Kṛṣṇa, You must accept them,
they’re better than Me.”

8
00:00:25,951 --> 00:00:28,782
That’s Her mood.

9
00:00:28,782 --> 00:00:32,877
She’s always promoting others,
recognising the devotion in others

10
00:00:32,877 --> 00:00:37,020
—the devotional potential in others—
and promoting them.

11
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:40,800
But Guru Mahārāj says on the basis
of what we find in the end of the Antya-līlā,

12
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:43,353
the very end of the Chaitanya-charitāmṛta,

13
00:00:43,353 --> 00:00:48,438
that sometimes She’s saying, 
“But there’s certain service only I can do,

14
00:00:48,438 --> 00:00:49,851
so I do that.”

15
00:00:49,851 --> 00:00:54,272
But otherwise, She’s promoting others.

16
00:00:56,027 --> 00:01:01,109
Once, when Guru Mahārāj’s secretaries,
who were like legitimate secretaries,

17
00:01:01,109 --> 00:01:04,463
they had to go to this place or that place, 
maybe get a new visa …

18
00:01:04,463 --> 00:01:05,752
doing some sevā.

19
00:01:05,752 --> 00:01:08,482
So, some devotee,

20
00:01:09,766 --> 00:01:13,239
very inexplicably or,

21
00:01:14,347 --> 00:01:18,017
surprisingly, became the secretary
for a short time.

22
00:01:18,017 --> 00:01:21,174
And every one was like, surprised,

23
00:01:21,174 --> 00:01:25,508
“So-and-so will be
Guru Mahārāj’s secretary?”

24
00:01:25,508 --> 00:01:29,615
and one of Guru Mahārāj’s …
part of his entourage,

25
00:01:29,615 --> 00:01:35,610
someone said, “Well, Mahāprabhu
wants to give everyone a chance.”

